            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": ", a devastating collision (while parked) resulted in it being transformed into a custom car that is truly one of a kind.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "src": "__GHOST_URL__/content/images/2020/06/1996-mitsubishi-3000gt-vr4-9-1.jpg",
        "caption": "Image Credit: Speed Digital LLC"
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "What you see here is a Mitsubishi 3000GT ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 0,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": "Spyder",
                "type": "text",
                "version": 1
              }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "type": "link",
            "rel": null,
            "target": null,
            "title": null,
            "url": "__GHOST_URL__/articles/handpicked/specially-built-ferrari-488-spyder/",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "  that has been customized to look like a Dodge Stealth; the 3000GT and Stealth were Japanese-made sister cars under Chrysler and Mitsubishi's Diamond-Star joint venture. According to the listing, this Mitsubishi had been parked in a driveway when it was hit and totaled. As rare as these ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 0,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": "Spyders",
                "type": "text",
                "version": 1
              }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "type": "link",
            "rel": null,
            "target": null,
            "title": null,
            "url": "__GHOST_URL__/articles/handpicked/james-deans-550-spyders-transaxle-is-up-for-sale/",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " are, we're glad the owner chose to create a custom build rather than sending this Japanese sports car off to the junkyard.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "In a partnership between Mitsubishi and ASC, the 3000GT coupe was assembled in Japan and then shipped to the U.S. where it was transformed into a convertible with an easy-to-use retractable hardtop making it the first such convertible that had been offered the U.S. since the 1959 Ford Fairlane Sunliner. In total, just 1,034 ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 0,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": "Spyders",
                "type": "text",
                "version": 1
              }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "type": "link",
            "rel": null,
            "target": null,
            "title": null,
            "url": "__GHOST_URL__/articles/news/barn-find-porsche-550-spyder/",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " were made over the Spyder's two model years (1995 and 1996), and the twin-turbo models are even rare with only 84 examples made in 1996; of those 84, just 21 were painted in white.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Of course, a Dodge Stealth convertible was never made, and that's where this custom creation comes into play. Rather than scrapping this rare-but-wrecked Mitsubishi, it was given a complete rebody to look like a Dodge Stealth. The convertible top, hood, rear decklid and doors appear to be carried over from the 3000GT Spyder, but everything else is what you'll find on a Stealth including the body cladding, wheels and bumpers. Even the Dodge Stealth airbag was added to the interior. This car was done up to look like the Dodge Stealth R/T twin turbo, which is a counterpart to the 3000GT VR-4 this car started its life as. These sports cars featured a 320-horsepower DOHC V6 under the hood, a six-speed manual transmission and all-wheel drive.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "As is the case with many custom cars, this Dodge Stealth R/T Twin Turbo Convertible (née Mitsubishi 3000GT Spyder VR-4 Spyder) comes with a reconstructed title due to its accident and subsequent rebody, and as such, it's being listed for sale through ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 0,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": "Classic Auto Mall",
                "type": "text",
                "version": 1
              }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "type": "link",
            "rel": null,
            "target": null,
            "title": null,
            "url": "https://buy.motorious.com/inventory/dealer/Classic+Auto+Mall",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " for $13,900. You can click ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 0,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": "HERE ",
                "type": "text",
                "version": 1
              }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "type": "link",
            "rel": null,
            "target": null,
            "title": null,
            "url": "https://buy.motorious.com/vehicles/197517/1996-mitsubishi-3000gt-vr4",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "to make an offer on this custom Mitsubishi, which is perhaps just a quick restoration away from being a show car.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
